Ten years ago yesterday, this girl left this earth. She had an infectious laugh . A specific posture when she lit up for the cameras, and such a sweetness most often. I used to mimic her affectionately among mutual friends... but I don’t do that anymore as she is gone and nobody wants to laugh along with the memory of someone so full of everything and nothing now. We miss you  #brittanymurphy.  I hope you have someone hugging your soul now. You gave great hugs. Be in peace little one. 🖤

Just try this. Tell the cynic to go pick up leaves and do the next right step.  I feel scattered and unable to connect the dots, what dots? I just need to connect a few and I am not even Wanting to. So I light a candle and pray and listen. I am burning all my candles at both ends and achieving nothing. I am sorry to all the people I haven’t thanked in person and social media. My son learned how to ride a bike with his dad yesterday. I wasn’t there. I was here. Lighting a candle. To all of us who can light a candle or whatever we need, and pray, and listen, I am whispering a thank you to all of you right here. #ilovedyoutoday. #pourlairscents @pourlair_scents 🖤. We can watch our children ride and laugh when we can. I cheer him and all of us on. From here.

As with any medication, there's a lot to consider. See the Important Safety Info and full Prescribing Info for Acthar Gel (repository corticotropin injection) at @acthar_gel. #sponsored
.
Found this video scrolling through my old photos and it made me reflect on how far I have come in my journey with MS. Around the time of my diagnosis last year, I had an MS attack while trying to find a DMT for everyday use. I remember feeling so overwhelmed with my life, on top of living with MS, trying to treat my MS attack. Communicating with my doctor about my MS treatment plan was so vital to my own journey. He told me that not all medications treat MS attacks and everyone’s experience is completely different. DMTs may not totally prevent MS attacks and treating attacks is a totally different process. Staying informed on treatment options has made me feel reassured in knowing that there may be a form of relief. I appreciate all of the love, support, and questions you guys have been sending me. If you want to learn more, check out my video describing my MS journey at ITookTheLead.com
.
What is Acthar Gel?
.
Acthar is a prescription treatment for adults with acute relapses or flares of multiple sclerosis (MS). Studies have shown Acthar Gel to be effective in speeding recovery from an MS relapse. However, there is no evidence that Acthar affects the ultimate outcome or natural history of the disease.
Acthar is injected beneath the skin or into the muscle.
.
SELECT IMPORTANT SAFETY INFORMATION
.
DO NOT take Acthar until you have talked to your doctor if you have any of the following conditions:
• A skin condition called scleroderma.
• Bone density loss or osteoporosis.
• Any infections, including fungal, bacterial, or viral.
• Eye infections, such as ocular herpes simplex.
• Had recent surgery.
.
Tell your doctor about any other health problems that you have. Give your doctor a complete list of medicines you are taking. Include all nonprescription medicines, vitamins, and herbal supplements that you are taking.
.
Please see additional Important Safety Information and full Prescribing Information @acthar_gel.
.

I’m proud to announce my partnership with @Novartis on their Innovation Prize: Assistive Tech for Multiple Sclerosis, which will award $250,000 for technology that makes the daily lives of those with MS disabilities easier. It feels really amazing to be able to announce this and engage great minds to come up with new technology for people living with disabilities. Tech has made my life with MS feel more manageable but there is still so much more that can be done. Great minds = great innovation! Learn more and apply at wired.com/msinnovationprize. #MSInnovationPrize #LivingWithMS #TechForGood #ad
